Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of cathode films on a solid oxide fuel cell electrolyte can be determined quantitatively by in situ infrared spectroscopy over a wide range of temperatures and partial oxygen pressures.
Titulo: Measuring Electrical Properties of Thin Film Fuel Cell Electrodes by In Situ Infrared Spectroscopy

Sentencas: This method allows measurement of the electrical conductivity of an electrode film on the electrolyte excluding leakage current effects through the substrate.
Titulo: Measuring Electrical Properties of Thin Film Fuel Cell Electrodes by In Situ Infrared Spectroscopy
